  "description": "John Milton has been off the grid for six months. Hunted by his former masters and haunted by his past, he resurfaces in the most dangerous city in the world: Ciudad Juárez, Mexico. It’s the perfect place to disappear—until Milton crosses paths with a fearless journalist investigating the cartels, and a girl who has seen too much. As rival gangs wage open war across the borderlands, Milton is dragged into a brutal conflict where life is cheap and death is a message. But the cartels have their own patron saint—Santa Muerte, Saint Death—and Milton has caught his attention. Now, with a price on his head and the world’s deadliest killers closing in, he must decide: keep running, or stand and fight in a city built on blood. Packed with relentless action, razor-sharp tension, and Mark Dawson’s trademark grit, Saint Death is a thriller that proves once again why John Milton is the man you call when you’re out of options. Read more",
